<br>
		<img alt="Jaggery Command Line" src="/themes/ROOT/img/commandline.png"/>
	</div>
</div>
<br/>
<div class="row-fluid">
	<div class="span12">
		<div class="page-header">
			<h2> The List Of Commands <a id="commands" class="bookmark"></a></h2>

		</div>

		<p>
			<code>
				&lt;script.jag&gt;
			</code>
			- Load Jaggery script (script.jag) from the current path.
			<br/>
			<br/>
			<code>
				Eg :- sh jaggery.sh script.jag
			</code>
		</p>

		<br/>
		<img alt="Jaggery Commands" src="/themes/ROOT/img/load.png"/>

		<p>
			<code>
				-help
			</code>
			&#150 Shows all the commands for help.
		</p>

		<p>
			<code>
				-quit
			</code>
			&#150 Quits the Jaggery command line (Only applicable for shell mode).
		</p>

		<p>
			<code>
				-shell
			</code>
			&#150 Enter into the shell mode (shell mode is described in the next section).
		</p>

		<p>
			<code>
				-version
			</code>
			&#150 Shows the current version of the Jaggery build.
		</p>
	</div>
</div>
